Thank you to the amazing ladies who created these looks. I‚Äôve linked their channels below, for you to find them and subscribe.  ‚ù§Ô∏è

Angie creates very detailed product reviews including extensive education on skincare and ingredients. I love her foundation reviews because she test them over several days with different primers and products to give a full 360 review on the foundation.

Michele creates tons of videos focused on Luxury Beauty reviews, hauls and new releases. She is the channel to watch before you purchase anything luxury. She uploads severals videos per week and has a thriving makeup loving community.

Chelsea's channel is all things beauty. She also focuses on hot new product releases and does tutorials where she shows you 2 different looks with one palette. She also has a series she does with Kelsee Briana Jai and Alicia Kinkysweat called Behind the Beauty where they interview brand owners, celebrity makeup artists, and other prominent figures in the Beauty Industry. Its such a great series!
Friends, I am so excited to share the True Beauty Palette with you! For our first eyeshadow palette, I wanted to create a neutral everyday palette that you could wear every shade.
The palette has 6 matte shades, and 6 shimmer shades. The shimmers are a soft satin shimmer, for a beautiful subtle sheen on the skin. Beautiful on all skin tones and skin textures.

The pop of color in the palette is KATE a gorgeous shimmer purple with pink shift. It can be worn alone on the lid, lower lash line or layered over any of the shades in the middle row to create the softest subtle shift of purple to the look.
I hope you love the palette as much as I do! Always filled with love and gratitude xoxo Lisa
Launches Thursday 11/10/2020 at 9am CST only at https://www.bkbeauty.com/

Hi Friends! I hope you enjoy this video. I hope this helps and answers all your questions regarding how to clean your brushes.

In regards to storing your brushes. I like to store mine in a brush cup standing upright and I also store my overflow brushes in a drawer but I have them laying flat in a drawer organizer tray I got from Target. The benefit to storing in a drawer is that they wont get dust on them if you have a home that has a lot of dust. I don't have an issue with my brushes on the counter , because I clean them about every 2 weeks and use them daily. If you store them in a drawer, I would recommend getting a tray that can separate them from other products you may store in your drawer so they don't get damaged. Personally I am not a fan of a brush roll unless I am traveling. They can easily damage the shape of the brush head especially your brushes that have a longer, fluffier head.
I clean my brushes about every 2 weeks. Foundation or concealer brushes may need weekly cleaning.

Hi Friends! I hope you enjoy this video. This is an honest and real look at my day. What I typically eat, and how I get in my exercise. A lot has changed in my diet and workout routine over the years. I have gone through phases where I punished myself with workouts (not enjoying it, but just overdoing it because I felt I needed to burn calories from over indulging the day before. I also use to be so restrictive in my diet, and didn't allow myself to enjoy some of the things I wanted. And if I did, I would over eat on them, because in my mind 1 cookie is equally as bad as 10, right?!?! I have such a healthier relationship with my body, and with food these days. I eat things that make me feel good, and I stay active by enjoying the things I love, my bike, running outside and barre classes. I may not be as tone and lean as I once was, but I can tell you I am a much happier person than I was in those years of my life. I hope this inspires you to treat and love yourself well. xoxox

BROWN EYES: I'm reading all the comments, and I did not mean to intentionally leave out brown eyes. My apologies for the oversight! Brown eyes are very fortunate in that really any color you prefer to wear will look nice with brown eyes. Blues, Emeralds, and Purples look exceptionally stunning on brown eyes.

Hi Friends! I get a lot of questions on Keratin Treatments. What exactly it is, how long does it last, is it worth it etc... I wanted to take you along with me on my recent appointment to show you the process and results. I do have to say that getting them back to back (Its been about 4 months since my last one) I can definitely tell I got better results this time than last (even though I did like it the first time, this time my hair seems a little better). I have had it done in the past (years ago) but never got them consistently.. I would go 6 months or more between. Depending on where you go, prices will vary but to give you an idea Gracie charges $350-$400. I hope you enjoy this video. Thank you for watching. xoxo Lisa

column1: Hi Friends! Thank you for watching! We had a great trip to NYC last week. It was short and sweet and nice to have a little time away from the kids and have a full day in NYC. Paul had a work trip so I just tagged along. We had 1 full day there and while he was working I explored the city with lots of shopping walking up and down 5th Avenue. I think the most impressive store I walked into was Saks 5th Avenue... on 5th Avenue. I felt like Pretty Woman,  minus the ""working girl"" ;) part and minus the mean sales ladies... so actually I guess I didn't feel like Pretty Woman. haha! I just felt a little out of place I guess. But it was such a beautiful store! Upstair they had a cafe and I asked for a coconut milk latte and while they didn't have Coconut Milk, they had OAT MILK. Say Wha??? Oat Milk?? Apparently that is the new thing.. you heard it here first. :) It was actually pretty good. :)
Anyhow...I hope you enjoy this video. Thank you for all your support and love...Lisa

column1: Hey friends! Thank you for watching! I get so many questions on my skincare routine. For the longest time I used R+F exclusively and didn't really switch anything up. I started trying new products maybe a year or so ago. I went through a few months where I was trying too much and realized I really needed to stick to the same products for a while and not mix it up so much. Its difficult to see what's working and what is not when you try too many products and switch it up too much. I've been using this combo of products for the last couple of months and I really like where my skin is at when I am using all of these together.
Leave your questions below. Thanks for watching! xoxo
Oh, I ended up having to cancel my trip to Cancun... my daughter has the flu! :(

column1: Hey friends! This video is extra special to me... I'm so happy to share these precious photos of my family with you (stick around to the very end). We have always taken family photos every year since my first daughter was born but last year, seemed to pass by and I never got around to scheduling them. It can be a lot of stress with young kids, planning the outfits, getting it all together, making sure the youngest has napped and is in good spirits... Gosh as I type that sentence I realize how trivial it all sounds... I found this year to be very easy, and stress free. I found the girls outfits at H&M, in a 20 minute shopping trip and I borrowed this sweater dress from a friend (I ended up ordering it for myself!:) And our photographer was amazing and go all of these photos in a 20 minute mini session!
I hope my tips for makeup for photography are helpful for your next photoshoot or any special occasion when you know you may be photographed.
Leave all your questions and comments below. Thank you for watching! xoxo

column1: Hey friends! How is it already the end of 2017?! Does anyone else feel like this year has just flown by?? I say that every year, I guess and every year it seems to fly by quicker and quicker. I have some exciting videos planned for December and really excited about entering 2018! I have some big news (well Big to me :)... As of Feb 1, I will be transitioning to a Full Time YouTuber. So crazy to think I've reached this point where I can pursue this a little more seriously than I have been able to by juggling so much the last 3 years. I feel truly fortunate and grateful. It's still a couple of months away, but I wanted to give my employment plenty of time to prepare for me to transition away. column1: Hey friends! An update on my daughter... I filmed this the day before we had her following up appointment with the Neurologist. She had an EEG the next day which looks at electrical activity in the brain. The results were normal and no unusual activity was monitored which was great news to hear! It still leaves us with little answers as to what caused her seizure, but the doctor said it is ""unlikely"" it will happen again. So at this point, we are just thankful for a good diagnosis, and hopeful it was a freak occurrence that won't happen again. I may only have 2 videos a week for the next couple of weeks while I try and catch up. Hope you like this one on my favorite products for September! Have a great week! xoxo ...Lisa

column1: Hey friends! Thank you for watching my videos. I've been curious about Dermaplaning for a while now and when my friend Allison Bingham offered for me to try out the service I thought this would be something you all might be curious about or interested in learning more about. A Dermaplane facial is basically an aggressive exfoliation to the skin using a blade to remove the top layer of dead skin cells, and all facial hair. Its pretty amazing and one that I will likely want to keep up with! In the video I answer all the typical questions about cost, maintenance and what it is. Hope you enjoy!
Disclosure: this video is not sponsored but services were complimentary. I chose this service because I felt this would be most interesting to my subscribers.

column1: I've included the workout details below:
MAIN WORKSET: 3- 5 ROUNDS with 45 Second Rest between rounds
Reverse Lunge Twist (30 seconds each side, 60 total)
Burbee Sprawl (30 seconds each side, 60 sec total)
Front Kick Thru (30 seconds each side, 60 seconds total)
Shin Box Extension (30 seconds each side, 60 sec total)
Shinbox Flow: Tripod Shinbox Extension (5 reps) to Half Pigeon Stretch (30 seconds hold)
Trainer at Onnit Academy, Austin TX

Hey friends! Thanks for watching! I'm so excited to share this workout with you. I recently discovered the Onnit Academy Gym here in Austin, and LOVE it! It's what I need right now to make real changes in my body. I love running and cycling but those are the only consistent exercises I do, so I'm really lacking strength and core training. I also have had problems with lower back pain so have been hesitant to do any heavy weighted exercises. The movements I did in the classes at Onnit, where like nothing I had done in a group exercise program. They were challenging, I was sweating, but I also felt like they were good for the supportive joints. Hard to explain, but really I just felt like I was maximizing my output with slower, controlled movements that i wasn't worried about throwing out my back while doing. I knew I wanted to do a workout video for you guys, and was so thrilled when they agreed to let me borrow Cristian to walk you through it. Really great stuff here! I'm leaving the workout with rep info down below.

column1: Hey friends! Thanks for watching! I've wanted to share this story in its own video for a while now. I talked about it in my Weight Loss Story video I posted a few years ago, but since a lot of you may not have been subscribed to my channel then, I thought this topic was a good one to address in a Feel Good Friday. This experience opened up my eyes to how toxic aspartame can be to our bodies. It was a very scary experience, and I wanted to share it with others. Now I'm not saying I NEVER have it anymore, but I do avoid it as much as possible. The only things I consume that still have it are a diet soda here and there. But I learned from this that just because something is 0 calories or sugar free, doesn't mean its helping in your weight loss attempts.

qGL887gSnrA,First Impression on the NEW Revlon FX Foundation for Mature Skin,"ALL INFO DOWN BELOW! Please subscribe before you leave!
Hey friends! Thanks for watching! When I walked by the new Revlon FX Foundation and Concealer and saw it was marketed for mature skin, I had to try it!

Sadly I was pretty disappointed in this foundation but I do love the concealer! I didn't do a follow up check up on this foundation like I normally do in Foundation Reviews, sorry! It was a hectic day and I didn't get a chance to check back in. Don't worry, my future foundation reviews will be my normal style where I check back in with updates.

But... I didn't like this foundation at all. It felt very sticky and I don't think it blurred lines at all on my skin like it claims to do. It also didn't cover well for my skin. I was not a fan. It reminded me of a very sticky, thick tinted moisturizer to be honest. The only positive to me on this is the SPF of 20. Other than that, I can't recommend this product. The concealer on the other hand is a different story! I really like it!
The Earrings I am wearing are by Kendra Scott. I couldn't find the style on her website to link but I am linking some other ear crawlers she has.

column2: Botox,"ALL INFO DOWN BELOW! Please subscribe before you leave!

column1: Hey guys! I am very hesitant to share this video. I know Botox is a sensitive subject, there are different opinions on the subject on both ends good and bad. But I did get it for the first time a few months ago, and decided to go back for my second treatment. I wanted to take you with me, show you the procedure and answer some common questions.

I am 34 years old and had been considering getting it for quite a while. I have a lot of friends who get it, and the results are not permanent so I became comfortable with trying it out. I was pretty blown away with the results (my first before and after photos are in the video).

I went back and forth on sharing this and opening myself up to criticism but decided to go ahead and post it.I can respect everyone's opinions and decisions as it comes to botox, or any plastic surgery and I hope people can respect mine.
Body Tonic Med Spa, Austin TX
Thank you all for your support! xo...Lisa",2017-05-28T14:00:02Z,PT10M9S,hd,2d,false,True,21151,537,0,161,public

7kfF2HDOEGk,"First Impression, Review and Demo: Estee Lauder Cushion Stick Foundation & Highligher","All info below... Don't forget to subscribe and let me know what foundations to review next!

I was so excited to try this foundation. When I first saw it online, I immediately started hunting down where I could get my hands on it first. I'm a fan of Estee Lauder's foundations (particularly their Double Wear full coverage liquid foundation) and also a fan of the cushion technology so I thought putting this into a stick applicator was genius! Honest review... I was disappointed in this product. While it's pretty when initially applied, I find the applicator almost pointless and the wearability is not long enough for me. Hope this video helps you in deciding whether this foundation is worth the purchase or not. Thanks for watching!
